modules.description: This module enables sending and receiving messages over sockets with optional attached file descriptors, using scatter-gather I/O for efficient data transfer. It operates on `Unix.file_descr` for sockets and handles `bytes` or `bytes array` for data, returning the number of bytes transferred along with any associated file descriptor. Concrete use cases include passing file descriptors between processes over Unix domain sockets and transmitting fragmented data in network protocols.
